quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  95,1,"By the fig and the olive."
  95,2,"By Mount Tûr of Sinai."
  95,3,"By this safe city{1}—",footnotes:1:Makkah.
  95,4,"surely, We created man in the best state,"
  95,5,"then We returned him to the lowest of the low,"
  95,6,"except those who attained faith and did righteous deeds, for for them is an unfailing reward."
  95,7,"So what makes you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>still deny the recompense?"
  95,8,"Is Allah not the Wisest of judges?"
  96,1,"Recite: In the name of your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord Who created—"
  96,2,"created man from a clinging form."
  96,3,"Recite: And your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is the Most Noble,"
  96,4,"the OneWho taught by the pen—"
  96,5,"taught man what he never knew."
  96,6,"But no! Indeed, man surely exceeds all limits,"
  96,7,"for he sees himself self-sufficient."
  96,8,"Indeed, to your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is the ultimate return."
  96,9,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>seen the one who forbids"
  96,10,"a servant when he prays?"
  96,11,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>seen whether he was rightly guided"
  96,12,"or commanded to mindfulness<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>?"
  96,13,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>seen whether he disbelieved and turned away?"
  96,14,"Has he not realized that Allah sees?"
  96,15,"But no! Surely, if he does not desist, We will drag<i class=""s"">(him) </i>by the forelock—"
  96,16,"a lying, wrongful forelock."
  96,17,"Let him call on his gang;"
  96,18,"We will call the guards of Hell."
  96,19,"But no! Do not obey him, but prostrate yourself and draw near."
